WEBVTT

00:00.125 --> 00:03.373
[♪♪♪]

00:03.398 --> 00:04.466
Coffee?

00:04.466 --> 00:05.800
[Brent grumbling]

00:05.800 --> 00:07.936
Someone's in
a bit of a mood.

00:07.936 --> 00:09.003
Ah, sorry.

00:09.003 --> 00:10.071
The wind storm last night

00:10.071 --> 00:12.207
blew some shingles
off my roof.

00:12.207 --> 00:13.808
Ah, so you need
new shingles.

00:13.808 --> 00:16.478
It also blew a tree
onto my roof.

00:16.478 --> 00:17.812
So you need a new roof?

00:17.812 --> 00:19.147
And a new tree,

00:19.147 --> 00:20.705
and let's not forget
about the shingles.

00:20.730 --> 00:22.350
That's a real boot
to the gutters.

00:22.350 --> 00:23.685
Boot to the gutters?

00:23.685 --> 00:24.752
Well, you know
what they say

00:24.752 --> 00:25.553
about the weather.

00:25.553 --> 00:28.756
Wait five minutes,
and my eggs are cold.

00:28.756 --> 00:30.892
That's not the saying.

00:30.892 --> 00:33.561
I just got sidetracked
by these cold eggs.

00:33.561 --> 00:34.896
A whole new roof?

00:34.896 --> 00:37.298
[sighs] What a kick
in the soffits.

00:37.298 --> 00:39.701
That'll put a dent
in your emergency fund.

00:39.701 --> 00:40.768
It might.

00:40.768 --> 00:42.637
If I had
an emergency fund,

00:42.637 --> 00:44.239
or a rainy day fund,

00:44.239 --> 00:47.175
or a sock in which I had
money socked away.

00:47.175 --> 00:49.043
That's a real
knee to the downspout.

00:49.043 --> 00:51.446
Have you been bingeing
the Property Brothers?

00:51.446 --> 00:53.848
I guess now is a good time
to tell you--

00:53.848 --> 00:54.916
We told you so!

00:54.916 --> 00:55.984
No!

00:55.984 --> 00:58.119
We put money away for you
when you were young.

00:58.119 --> 00:59.454
That's his inheritance.

00:59.454 --> 01:03.191
Give it to him now,
you reward bad behaviour.

01:03.191 --> 01:05.593
A broken roof
is bad behaviour?

01:05.593 --> 01:06.928
Careful, Oscar.

01:06.928 --> 01:08.796
You might be motivating
Brent to knock you off

01:08.796 --> 01:10.665
just to collect
that inheritance.

01:10.665 --> 01:12.800
Over my dead body.

01:12.800 --> 01:14.135
That's what
I'm saying.

01:14.135 --> 01:16.004
I would never do that.

01:16.004 --> 01:17.605
Now, eat your poison eggs.

01:17.605 --> 01:18.940
I mean, cold eggs.

01:18.940 --> 01:22.944
♪ You think
there's not a lot goin' on ♪

01:22.944 --> 01:26.414
♪ Look closer, baby
you're so wrong ♪

01:26.414 --> 01:29.797
[♪♪♪]

01:29.822 --> 01:31.438
So you think
the lyrics to that song

01:31.463 --> 01:34.533
are "won't you take me
to Monkey Town"?

01:34.558 --> 01:35.353
Exactly.

01:35.378 --> 01:37.358
Who would want to be
taken to Funky Town?

01:37.358 --> 01:39.761
Probably smells like
bad breath and armpits.

01:39.761 --> 01:41.095
You think a town
full of monkeys

01:41.095 --> 01:42.163
isn't gonna have a funk?

01:42.163 --> 01:44.032
Sure, it might
curl your lip a little,

01:44.032 --> 01:46.701
but, hey, monkeys!

01:46.701 --> 01:48.303
I don't think
that's true.

01:48.303 --> 01:50.972
I am just telling you
what I read.

01:50.972 --> 01:52.574
Ah, thank god.

01:52.574 --> 01:53.349
A real conversation

01:53.374 --> 01:55.243
that doesn't
involve primates.

01:55.243 --> 01:56.578
Or have I
spoke too soon?

01:56.578 --> 01:57.645
I read a blog

01:57.645 --> 01:58.980
that said people
lie to the police

01:58.980 --> 02:00.582
90% of the time.

02:00.582 --> 02:02.717
That can't be true
in Dog River.

02:02.717 --> 02:05.920
Everyone is so close-knit
and caring.

02:05.920 --> 02:07.789
Why would anyone
lie to us?

02:07.789 --> 02:08.856
'Cause you're cops.

02:08.856 --> 02:10.276
Didn't you hear
what Karen said?

02:10.301 --> 02:13.127
Yeah, it's all tickets,
and rules, and warnings,

02:13.127 --> 02:15.236
and second warnings,
and final warnings

02:15.261 --> 02:16.064
with you guys.

02:16.064 --> 02:17.665
And statistically
speaking,

02:17.665 --> 02:19.534
most people have
broken some law

02:19.534 --> 02:20.143
in the past.

02:20.168 --> 02:22.203
I don't think
it's most people.

02:22.203 --> 02:25.139
I believe the majority
of citizens are law-abiding.

02:25.139 --> 02:25.940
You also believe

02:25.940 --> 02:27.496
there's a place
called Monkey Town.

02:27.520 --> 02:31.487
[♪♪♪]

02:31.512 --> 02:32.690
Gimme one good reason

02:32.715 --> 02:34.482
why we shouldn't
give Brent his money.

02:34.482 --> 02:35.817
You're lookin' at it.

02:35.817 --> 02:37.418
That doesn't
make any sense.

02:37.418 --> 02:40.622
It makes as much sense
as giving him the money does.

02:40.622 --> 02:44.092
Honestly, you argue
like a kindergarten dropout.

02:44.092 --> 02:45.693
I don't need your permission.

02:45.693 --> 02:46.761
Permission for what?

02:46.761 --> 02:48.363
To give Brent his money.

02:48.363 --> 02:51.032
Are we still
talking about that?

02:51.032 --> 02:52.634
I'm going to find
a more quiet place

02:52.634 --> 02:53.967
to read my paper.

02:53.991 --> 02:57.825
[♪♪♪]

02:57.850 --> 02:59.307
Third National Trust.

02:59.307 --> 03:01.976
Yes, how do I go about
closing an account

03:01.976 --> 03:03.576
opened by an idiot?

03:03.600 --> 03:06.222
[♪♪♪]

03:06.247 --> 03:07.849
Something
bothering you, Hank?

03:07.849 --> 03:08.916
Huh?

03:08.916 --> 03:10.785
Ah, I'm just thinking
about something

03:10.785 --> 03:12.385
Karen and Davis said
about lying.

03:12.410 --> 03:13.721
Oh, no.

03:13.721 --> 03:15.056
Are they on to us?

03:15.056 --> 03:16.124
On to us?

03:16.124 --> 03:18.793
Do they suspect anything
about you and me

03:18.793 --> 03:20.128
and our "secret"?

03:20.128 --> 03:21.432
Our secret?

03:21.457 --> 03:23.598
I, uh... I don't think so.

03:23.598 --> 03:24.367
Good.

03:24.392 --> 03:25.733
You did the right thing

03:25.733 --> 03:27.068
by coming to me
about this.

03:27.068 --> 03:28.136
Uh, this being...?

03:28.136 --> 03:30.875
You, me, that thing
that happened.

03:30.900 --> 03:33.182
The cops
can never find out.

03:33.207 --> 03:34.275
Well, I guarantee

03:34.275 --> 03:35.968
they won't hear
about it from me.

03:35.992 --> 03:39.465
[♪♪♪]

03:39.490 --> 03:41.749
I was just on the phone

03:41.749 --> 03:43.351
with Third National Trust,

03:43.351 --> 03:45.753
and there's no account
set up for Brent.

03:45.753 --> 03:46.821
Why would there be?

03:46.821 --> 03:48.423
I put it in the farmer's bank.

03:48.423 --> 03:49.757
You buried it?

03:49.757 --> 03:51.359
Yeah, in the yard.

03:51.359 --> 03:54.829
You can't trust
those three-piece shifty stiffs

03:54.829 --> 03:55.630
at the bank.

03:55.630 --> 03:57.231
The money's safer
in the ground.

03:57.231 --> 03:59.367
How is it supposed to grow?

03:59.367 --> 04:01.502
You dig it up,
take it to the bank,

04:01.502 --> 04:03.104
and tell them how long
it's been there,

04:03.104 --> 04:04.439
and they pay you interest.

04:04.439 --> 04:06.642
That's not how a bank works.

04:06.667 --> 04:08.418
Look at Mrs. Rockefeller,

04:08.443 --> 04:11.112
giving free lessons
on high finance.

04:11.112 --> 04:14.144
I find it hard to believe
people lie to us.

04:14.169 --> 04:15.237
Are you calling me
a liar?

04:15.262 --> 04:18.052
Look, if you want to know
if someone is lying to you,

04:18.052 --> 04:19.120
watch their eyes.

04:19.120 --> 04:20.988
If a person looks up
and to the left,

04:20.988 --> 04:22.857
they're using their imagination.

04:22.857 --> 04:24.192
If they look up
and to the right,

04:24.192 --> 04:25.793
they're using an actual memory.

04:25.793 --> 04:26.861
I didn't know that.

04:26.861 --> 04:27.662
I did.

04:27.662 --> 04:28.463
She's lying.

04:28.463 --> 04:29.797
She looked up
and to the left.

04:29.797 --> 04:30.598
I wasn't lying,

04:30.598 --> 04:31.399
I was just...

04:31.399 --> 04:33.801
looking at a bird
over there.

04:35.403 --> 04:36.471
Another way
you can tell

04:36.471 --> 04:38.312
is if they kick at the dirt
with their feet.

04:38.337 --> 04:39.113
[sighs] Okay!

04:39.138 --> 04:40.210
I didn't know.

04:40.235 --> 04:42.318
So there's other ways
to tell if people lie?

04:42.343 --> 04:43.945
Tons.

04:43.945 --> 04:46.609
Hey, Ike, how's that rash?

04:46.634 --> 04:47.702
It's good,
it's good.

04:49.016 --> 04:51.419
When people repeat themselves,
they're often lying.

04:51.419 --> 04:53.020
So...

04:53.020 --> 04:54.088
So don't touch Ike.

04:54.088 --> 04:57.024
I wish we could afford
a portable lie detector.

04:57.024 --> 04:58.359
We have Wanda.

04:58.359 --> 04:59.160
She's portable.

04:59.160 --> 05:01.028
You can't afford me,
either.

05:01.028 --> 05:02.630
Buy you lunch?

05:02.630 --> 05:03.411
Let's go, boss.

05:03.435 --> 05:06.075
[♪♪♪]

05:06.100 --> 05:07.168
Okay, here I am.

05:07.168 --> 05:07.969
What's so important

05:07.969 --> 05:10.307
that you couldn't tell me
over the phone?

05:10.332 --> 05:10.955
Whoa,

05:10.980 --> 05:14.108
Lacey was just joking
about murdering Dad.

05:14.108 --> 05:16.511
I need you to help me
dig up your trust fund.

05:16.511 --> 05:19.180
Your idiot father
buried it in the back yard.

05:19.180 --> 05:21.315
Because
of course he did.

05:21.315 --> 05:23.451
You know, Lacey's
murder idea--

05:23.451 --> 05:25.586
It's still on the table.

05:25.586 --> 05:26.921
I'm nervous.

05:26.921 --> 05:28.790
Should we really
be doing this?

05:28.790 --> 05:29.857
Better to know
the truth

05:29.857 --> 05:31.192
than to keep
wondering.

05:31.192 --> 05:33.327
Oftentimes,
people have personal signs

05:33.327 --> 05:34.128
that show they're lying,

05:34.128 --> 05:35.463
like a tell in poker,

05:35.463 --> 05:37.064
but there are general signs.

05:37.064 --> 05:39.734
Watch for lip-biting
or exaggerated hand gestures.

05:39.734 --> 05:40.802
Let's run a test.

05:40.802 --> 05:43.204
Hey, Lanny, did you get
that tail light fixed

05:43.204 --> 05:44.005
on your truck yet?

05:45.072 --> 05:46.407
Yeah, I got it fixed.

05:46.407 --> 05:47.208
Face-touching.

05:47.208 --> 05:48.276
That's a lie.

05:48.276 --> 05:49.343
How could he?!

05:49.343 --> 05:50.945
I'm gonna try
another one.

05:50.945 --> 05:53.347
Hey, Ravi, how's
the Reuben sandwich?

05:53.347 --> 05:54.148
Oh, my god,

05:54.148 --> 05:56.017
so good, so good.

05:56.017 --> 05:57.351
I highly recommend it.

05:57.351 --> 05:58.419
Two thumbs up.

05:58.419 --> 05:59.487
He's telling
the truth.

05:59.487 --> 06:01.088
But he repeated
himself.

06:01.088 --> 06:02.690
And he touched
his face.

06:02.690 --> 06:04.292
Yeah, but I had
the Reuben yesterday,

06:04.292 --> 06:07.228
and it was amazing,
so...

06:07.228 --> 06:09.897
Are you seeing
what I'm seeing?

06:09.897 --> 06:12.033
Yes, people love
your Reuben.

06:12.033 --> 06:13.100
No!

06:13.100 --> 06:14.168
Well, yes,

06:14.168 --> 06:15.770
but the cops
are using Wanda

06:15.770 --> 06:16.838
to suss out liars.

06:16.838 --> 06:17.638
Cool.

06:17.638 --> 06:18.973
Not cool!

06:18.973 --> 06:20.842
They might uncover our secret.

06:20.842 --> 06:21.909
Right.

06:21.909 --> 06:22.977
That secret we have.

06:22.977 --> 06:25.112
Uh, yeah,
I wouldn't worry about it.

06:25.112 --> 06:27.248
It's not like Wanda's
an expert or anything.

06:27.248 --> 06:28.049
Yes, she is!

06:28.049 --> 06:29.116
She's an expert
at everything.

06:29.116 --> 06:30.718
She's like a machine.

06:30.718 --> 06:33.921
We have to figure out
how to beat the machine.

06:33.921 --> 06:34.989
Yeah.

06:34.989 --> 06:35.790
Well, let's start

06:35.790 --> 06:38.192
with a couple
of Reuben sandwiches.

06:38.192 --> 06:39.546
I hear good things.

06:39.570 --> 06:41.429
[♪♪♪]

06:42.007 --> 06:44.217
[♪♪♪]

06:44.242 --> 06:46.406
I don't know where
your father buried the money,

06:46.422 --> 06:48.290
and he's not talking, either.

06:48.290 --> 06:50.914
So we're just randomly
digging up the yard?

06:50.961 --> 06:51.762
Not exactly.

06:51.762 --> 06:54.965
He said he put it
in the farmer's bank.

06:56.030 --> 06:57.068
Back in the day,

06:57.093 --> 06:58.702
when farmers buried money
on their land,

06:58.702 --> 07:01.372
they'd put it in a place
where they could watch over it

07:01.372 --> 07:03.507
from a door or window.

07:03.507 --> 07:06.977
So starting
from this door...

07:06.977 --> 07:10.981
That tree is probably
the reference point Oscar used.

07:10.981 --> 07:13.651
We just dig around that tree
and see if it's there.

07:13.651 --> 07:14.718
If it's there?

07:14.718 --> 07:16.587
You want me
to do manual labour

07:16.587 --> 07:18.189
based on speculation?

07:18.189 --> 07:19.523
What am I,
a prospector?

07:19.523 --> 07:23.260
Look, do you want
the $250 or not?

07:23.260 --> 07:24.328
250?

07:24.328 --> 07:25.930
Well, I guess
we can stop

07:25.930 --> 07:27.798
tossing the word
"treasure" around.

07:29.934 --> 07:32.951
[groans] We've been
digging for hours.

07:32.976 --> 07:35.279
It's got to be here
somewhere.

07:35.304 --> 07:36.357
Does it, though?

07:36.382 --> 07:39.022
I mean, using a tree
as a reference is logical.

07:39.047 --> 07:41.984
Dad probably used a puddle
or a bird.

07:41.984 --> 07:43.585
Warmer...

07:43.585 --> 07:44.920
Warmer.

07:44.920 --> 07:45.988
[giggles]

07:45.988 --> 07:47.856
Are you saying
this is the spot?

07:47.856 --> 07:48.657
I'm saying

07:48.657 --> 07:49.992
that you've been
digging so much

07:49.992 --> 07:51.860
that you're
getting warmer,

07:51.860 --> 07:52.928
and sweatier, too.

07:52.928 --> 07:55.330
I was sweating
before I got here.

07:55.330 --> 07:57.733
You probably don't even remember
where it's buried.

07:57.733 --> 07:58.534
I don't need to.

07:58.534 --> 08:00.936
I was smart enough
to leave myself a clue.

08:00.936 --> 08:02.804
There's a clue?

08:03.990 --> 08:05.058
No.

08:05.207 --> 08:07.609
We can't let Wanda
catch us in a lie.

08:07.609 --> 08:09.211
It'll open up
a whole can of worms,

08:09.211 --> 08:10.812
and the next thing
you know,

08:10.812 --> 08:11.880
our secret is out.

08:11.880 --> 08:12.948
Right.

08:12.948 --> 08:14.550
Our worm secret.

08:14.550 --> 08:16.151
Maybe if I don't show
any emotion,

08:16.151 --> 08:18.820
Wanda will have
nothing to read.

08:20.519 --> 08:21.621
Hey, Lacey,

08:21.646 --> 08:22.980
this sugar's empty.

08:23.005 --> 08:23.621
Yes.

08:23.646 --> 08:26.049
Sugar is lacking
from that container.

08:26.074 --> 08:28.743
The Reuben comes
with fries or a salad.

08:28.901 --> 08:30.503
Can I substitute soup?

08:30.566 --> 08:31.667
Affirmative.

08:31.692 --> 08:33.027
I will allow it.

08:33.052 --> 08:34.120
What kind of soup
do you have?

08:34.145 --> 08:36.013
Chicken noodle?
Tomato?

08:36.038 --> 08:39.775
I will provide
available soup.

08:40.709 --> 08:42.844
Mission accomplished.

08:42.844 --> 08:43.912
Really?

08:43.912 --> 08:46.582
Was your mission
to make Wanda suspicious?

08:47.916 --> 08:49.785
Aah! See?

08:49.785 --> 08:51.386
She's a machine!

08:51.386 --> 08:52.988
I've seen
a lot of cop movies

08:52.988 --> 08:54.323
and a lot
of machine movies,

08:54.323 --> 08:55.924
and one that was both.

08:55.924 --> 08:56.992
RoboCop.

08:56.992 --> 08:58.060
My point is,

08:58.060 --> 08:59.928
to beat
the lie detector,

08:59.928 --> 09:01.653
you just lie
about everything.

09:01.678 --> 09:02.745
Hey, Hank,

09:02.770 --> 09:03.571
come here.

09:03.596 --> 09:05.198
Watch this.

09:06.602 --> 09:08.470
What's with Lacey?

09:08.470 --> 09:09.367
Is she okay?

09:09.392 --> 09:09.926
Oh, yeah.

09:10.072 --> 09:11.406
She's just freaked out

09:11.406 --> 09:13.542
because it's gonna rain lava
this afternoon,

09:13.542 --> 09:16.211
and she left her flock
of emotional support camels

09:16.211 --> 09:17.924
grazing in her hemp field.

09:17.949 --> 09:18.760
By the way,

09:18.785 --> 09:21.989
today's special
is rhinoceros burgers.

09:23.034 --> 09:24.830
What was that?

09:25.020 --> 09:27.422
Lacey appears to be
on some kind of sedative.

09:27.422 --> 09:29.825
My guess, horse tranquilizer.

09:29.825 --> 09:30.685
And Hank?

09:30.710 --> 09:31.778
Hank's an idiot.

09:31.803 --> 09:32.997
She's not lying.

09:33.059 --> 09:35.939
[♪♪♪]

09:35.964 --> 09:37.566
So what do we do now?

09:37.566 --> 09:40.235
Just stand around
these 41 holes we've dug?

09:40.235 --> 09:43.171
Don't worry, I have a plan.

09:43.171 --> 09:44.239
Couldn't you have
thought of this plan

09:44.239 --> 09:46.252
before we dug
41 holes?

09:46.277 --> 09:48.946
Back from
my afternoon nap.

09:49.155 --> 09:50.223
[giggles]

09:50.248 --> 09:51.315
Have you two
given up yet?

09:51.446 --> 09:52.781
We were going to,

09:52.781 --> 09:54.116
but then you gave us
the clue.

09:54.116 --> 09:55.717
I did not.

09:55.717 --> 09:56.785
Not directly,

09:56.785 --> 09:58.387
but you talk
in your sleep.

09:58.387 --> 10:00.789
We went and got the clue
before you woke up.

10:01.692 --> 10:04.361
Ah, you're pullin' my cork.

10:06.128 --> 10:07.729
I just remembered,

10:07.729 --> 10:09.865
there's something
I gotta go do.

10:09.865 --> 10:12.000
Aren't you
a crafty weasel?

10:12.000 --> 10:13.068
Come on.

10:13.068 --> 10:15.470
Clueless is gonna
lead us to the clue.

10:15.494 --> 10:22.386
[♪♪♪]

10:22.411 --> 10:24.012
A-ha! I knew it.

10:24.012 --> 10:25.881
She was bluffing.

10:25.905 --> 10:31.194
[♪♪♪]

10:31.219 --> 10:34.690
He actually hid the clue
in a box marked "clue."

10:34.690 --> 10:36.291
I'm afraid to see
what he hid

10:36.291 --> 10:37.609
in the "Kerplunk" game.

10:37.633 --> 10:41.605
[♪♪♪]

10:41.630 --> 10:43.453
Hey, Lacey,
you wanted to see me?

10:43.478 --> 10:44.546
Uh, no.

10:44.571 --> 10:46.143
Ah, that's weird.

10:46.168 --> 10:48.837
I got a text from Wanda
that said you wanted to see me.

10:48.837 --> 10:50.706
[gasps] Oh, no.

10:50.706 --> 10:52.841
I bet it's some kind
of trick.

10:52.841 --> 10:53.909
Why don't you ask her?

10:54.976 --> 10:56.044
[yelps] Aah! Dammit!

10:56.044 --> 10:57.379
Now that
I have you here,

10:57.379 --> 10:58.180
I want to know

10:58.180 --> 10:59.514
why you two have been
acting weird

10:59.514 --> 11:00.849
in front of the cops.

11:00.849 --> 11:02.718
Uh, no reason.

11:02.718 --> 11:04.586
Hmm, no eye contact.

11:04.586 --> 11:05.387
Fidgeting.

11:05.387 --> 11:06.455
Pants on fire.

11:06.455 --> 11:07.522
Fine.

11:07.522 --> 11:08.857
There is something
going on,

11:08.857 --> 11:10.563
but we're not talking.

11:10.588 --> 11:11.388
Right, Hank?

11:11.413 --> 11:12.214
Not a word.

11:12.239 --> 11:15.238
You may be this big-shot
human lie detector,

11:15.263 --> 11:17.266
but you're getting
nothing from us.

11:17.291 --> 11:18.657
We're rock solid.

11:18.682 --> 11:19.483
That's right.

11:19.508 --> 11:21.110
Like a salad of rocks.

11:21.135 --> 11:23.537
I said "solid,"
not "salad."

11:25.841 --> 11:26.641
Follow me.

11:27.008 --> 11:30.459
I'm going to crack you
like a 12-year-old peanut.

11:30.484 --> 11:31.818
Let's do this!

11:31.843 --> 11:33.178
You think I can't?

11:33.227 --> 11:36.430
There's a reason they call me
the nutcracker!

11:36.455 --> 11:38.195
Actually,
there's a few reasons

11:38.220 --> 11:40.355
they call me the nutcracker.

11:40.355 --> 11:41.721
[groaning]

11:41.746 --> 11:43.266
There's so many
ways to show

11:43.291 --> 11:45.160
people are lying to you.

11:45.160 --> 11:48.363
Yeah, Wanda's cheat sheet
is more like a cheat essay.

11:48.363 --> 11:51.299
Good afternoon,
officers!

11:51.299 --> 11:53.969
Anything about annoying
sing-songy greetings?

11:53.969 --> 11:56.371
No, but she did
gesture wildly.

11:56.371 --> 11:58.240
It's called "waving."

11:58.240 --> 11:59.307
A lie's a lie.

11:59.307 --> 12:00.642
Helen hates you.

12:00.642 --> 12:01.443
Me?

12:01.443 --> 12:03.044
You're over-reacting.

12:03.044 --> 12:04.913
They can't be lying
about everything.

12:04.913 --> 12:07.315
But who knows what's a lie
and what's the truth?

12:07.315 --> 12:11.586
Maybe Lacey's lunch special
was Rhino Burgers.

12:11.586 --> 12:12.387
Hiya, Karen.

12:12.387 --> 12:13.989
Lookin' sharp, Davis.

12:13.989 --> 12:16.124
[fly buzzing]

12:16.124 --> 12:17.192
Face-touching.

12:17.192 --> 12:19.060
Nice try, Lanny!

12:19.060 --> 12:21.463
You lying son-of-a-bitch.

12:21.487 --> 12:23.040
[♪♪♪]

12:23.064 --> 12:24.132
We could be out there

12:24.132 --> 12:26.001
digging up your money
right now.

12:26.001 --> 12:27.068
Can I help it

12:27.068 --> 12:28.403
if espionage
makes me hungry?

12:28.403 --> 12:30.806
Everything
makes you hungry.

12:30.806 --> 12:32.674
They have the red envelope.

12:32.674 --> 12:35.343
Damn me
and my nap chatter.

12:35.343 --> 12:36.945
[grunting]

12:37.746 --> 12:38.814
A-ha!

12:42.017 --> 12:43.618
Where did this come from?

12:43.618 --> 12:44.953
[TV show plays]:
Coming up next,

12:44.953 --> 12:47.355
unravel the mysteries
and danger

12:47.355 --> 12:50.292
on... The Night Ninjas!

12:50.292 --> 12:54.478
[strumming ukulele]

12:54.503 --> 12:56.698
[wincing] Oh...

12:56.698 --> 12:58.300
Right.

12:58.300 --> 12:59.634
Forgot about that.

12:59.634 --> 13:02.037
I also forgot
where I buried that money.

13:02.037 --> 13:05.507
I have never felt
so raw and vulnerable

13:05.507 --> 13:06.575
in my life.

13:06.575 --> 13:09.244
What about that time
you and I drank wine,

13:09.244 --> 13:10.312
listened to Whitney,

13:10.312 --> 13:12.180
and you poured
your heart out about--

13:12.180 --> 13:14.316
That's a different
kind of vulnerable.

13:14.316 --> 13:15.148
Coffee?

13:15.173 --> 13:16.775
I don't know,
is it?

13:16.985 --> 13:18.320
Can we trust you?

13:18.320 --> 13:19.654
I'm sorry.

13:19.654 --> 13:21.790
It's... it's been
an emotional day.

13:21.790 --> 13:24.726
The special isn't even
rhino burgers, is it?

13:24.726 --> 13:25.527
Is it?!

13:25.527 --> 13:26.577
Steak sandwich,

13:26.602 --> 13:27.874
and that's the honest truth.

13:27.929 --> 13:28.997
You don't know

13:28.997 --> 13:31.921
how much the honest truth
means right now.

13:31.946 --> 13:34.578
I found out Won has been
selling me oranges

13:34.603 --> 13:36.471
and telling me
they're kumquats.

13:36.471 --> 13:37.806
Who does that?

13:37.806 --> 13:40.475
Maybe some people
have a reason

13:40.475 --> 13:42.344
for being... misleading.

13:42.344 --> 13:44.212
At least
you're honest with us.

13:44.212 --> 13:45.528
Yeah, Lacey.

13:45.553 --> 13:47.688
You're a good friend.

13:47.713 --> 13:48.622
Yes.

13:48.647 --> 13:49.448
I...

13:49.473 --> 13:50.541
friend...

13:50.566 --> 13:51.633
soup?

13:52.230 --> 13:54.899
[grunting]

13:55.423 --> 13:57.025
[groans]
Another dead end.

13:57.025 --> 14:00.228
This is a lot of work
for 250 bucks.

14:00.228 --> 14:01.296
I'm digging for, like...

14:01.296 --> 14:02.364
a buck a hole.

14:02.364 --> 14:04.232
Read the clue again.

14:04.232 --> 14:05.300
All it says

14:05.300 --> 14:06.948
is "when we were married".

14:06.973 --> 14:08.283
August 21st.

14:08.503 --> 14:10.639
That's eight and 21.

14:10.639 --> 14:12.507
We've paced out
eight and 21 steps

14:12.507 --> 14:14.642
in every possible
direction,

14:14.667 --> 14:15.443
and nothing.

14:15.443 --> 14:17.312
Why would he make that a clue?

14:17.312 --> 14:18.380
How sure are we

14:18.380 --> 14:20.248
that he even knows the date
you got married?

14:20.248 --> 14:21.583
You're right.

14:21.583 --> 14:23.718
I've had to remind him
of our anniversary

14:23.718 --> 14:25.854
every year since our wedding.

14:25.854 --> 14:27.455
I'm out of ideas.

14:27.455 --> 14:29.324
Should we check
the Kerplunk box?

14:29.324 --> 14:30.942
I'd rather not.

14:30.966 --> 14:32.966
[♪♪♪]

14:34.057 --> 14:37.184
[♪♪♪]

14:37.209 --> 14:40.146
Hank, Hank, Hank.

14:40.246 --> 14:43.059
I was impressed with
the little "lie-a-thon"

14:43.084 --> 14:44.419
you put on for the cops,

14:44.444 --> 14:47.559
but that strategy
isn't gonna work on me.

14:47.584 --> 14:48.450
Good.

14:48.475 --> 14:51.411
How about we drop
this dancing dog

14:51.436 --> 14:52.770
and prancing pony show,

14:52.795 --> 14:54.931
and you tell me what's going on?

14:54.937 --> 14:56.805
I haven't got a clue.

14:56.954 --> 14:58.289
Huh.

14:58.289 --> 14:59.624
Pupils are fixed.

14:59.624 --> 15:01.225
Muscles relaxed.

15:01.225 --> 15:02.601
Breathing is regular.

15:02.626 --> 15:03.961
Breath is rank.

15:03.986 --> 15:05.854
What is this, a physical
or an interrogation?

15:06.030 --> 15:06.910
Get on with it.

15:06.935 --> 15:09.846
Ooh, you're cool
as a Christmas cucumber.

15:09.871 --> 15:11.740
That's because
I need your help.

15:11.903 --> 15:12.970
You need my help?

15:12.970 --> 15:13.785
Yeah.

15:13.810 --> 15:14.878
Lacey and I have a secret,

15:14.903 --> 15:16.683
and I can't remember what it is,

15:16.708 --> 15:17.878
and it's driving me crazy.

15:17.903 --> 15:21.106
So I need you to dig deep
into my cerebral vortex,

15:21.245 --> 15:23.915
scratch around,
and help me figure it out.

15:23.915 --> 15:25.249
Are you playing me?

15:25.249 --> 15:27.652
I am 100%
not playing you.

15:27.652 --> 15:29.253
Well played.

15:29.253 --> 15:31.601
This is like top-drawer
three-dimensional chess.

15:31.626 --> 15:32.960
I don't have time
to learn chess!

15:33.162 --> 15:34.820
Get in there and
start poking around.

15:34.845 --> 15:36.180
Oh, you'd like that,
wouldn't you?

15:36.205 --> 15:37.236
I'm begging you.

15:37.261 --> 15:38.863
What the hell is going on?

15:38.863 --> 15:39.931
I don't know!

15:39.931 --> 15:42.066
[both screaming]

15:42.066 --> 15:43.401
The nerve of you two,

15:43.401 --> 15:46.070
stealing my clue
to dig up your money.

15:46.070 --> 15:47.405
You said it yourself.

15:47.405 --> 15:48.206
It's his money,

15:48.206 --> 15:49.540
and we're going
to find it.

15:49.540 --> 15:50.341
Ha!

15:50.341 --> 15:51.943
You can't figure it out.

15:51.943 --> 15:53.087
We will eventually.

15:53.112 --> 15:54.053
Maybe
if you tell me,

15:54.078 --> 15:55.146
I'll help.

15:55.146 --> 15:57.815
You don't know
what the clue is?

15:57.815 --> 15:59.417
You don't remember.

15:59.417 --> 16:02.086
All I had to remember
was where I hid it.

16:02.086 --> 16:03.955
If you tell me the clue,

16:03.955 --> 16:06.090
I'll tell you where I buried
your ukulele.

16:06.090 --> 16:08.226
You buried my ukulele?

16:08.226 --> 16:10.094
You told me it was stolen!

16:10.094 --> 16:11.460
By Night Ninjas!

16:11.485 --> 16:12.952
Look, Oscar,

16:12.983 --> 16:14.899
you don't know
what the clue is,

16:14.899 --> 16:16.234
and we can't
figure it out.

16:16.234 --> 16:18.369
I think we have
to work together,

16:18.369 --> 16:19.971
or the money
will be lost forever.

16:21.124 --> 16:22.192
All right,

16:22.373 --> 16:24.776
he can have
his stupid money.

16:24.776 --> 16:25.576
Finally.

16:25.576 --> 16:29.530
Okay, the clue is
"When we were married."

16:29.555 --> 16:30.623
Oh, right!

16:30.915 --> 16:32.784
Six,
then three.

16:32.784 --> 16:35.720
Six and three
is June 3rd.

16:35.720 --> 16:37.321
We weren't married
in June.

16:37.321 --> 16:40.471
We were married on
a Saturday at 3:00.

16:40.496 --> 16:42.072
Sixth day.
3:00 p.m.

16:42.393 --> 16:44.262
I can't believe
you forgot.

16:44.262 --> 16:45.863
I'll go pace it out.

16:45.863 --> 16:48.680
And tell me where
you buried my ukulele!

16:48.705 --> 16:50.307
Go ask
the Night Ninjas!

16:50.668 --> 16:53.337
Nobody can find
the Night Ninjas.

16:53.337 --> 16:54.766
That's
their whole thing.

16:54.790 --> 16:58.491
[♪♪♪]

16:58.516 --> 16:59.992
Did Wanda
get it out of you?

17:00.017 --> 17:00.817
Don't feel bad.

17:01.078 --> 17:02.680
She's a machine.

17:02.680 --> 17:04.890
A tiny,
terrifying machine.

17:04.915 --> 17:06.124
She did her best,

17:06.149 --> 17:07.484
but it's still
locked in there.

17:07.752 --> 17:11.222
Look, this secret
is obviously eating you up.

17:11.222 --> 17:13.357
Maybe you should
confess it to me,

17:13.357 --> 17:15.413
and then I'll confess it
back to you,

17:15.438 --> 17:16.480
and we'll all feel better.

17:17.094 --> 17:18.309
Not all of us.

17:18.334 --> 17:19.402
Follow me.

17:19.426 --> 17:21.341
[♪♪♪]

17:21.365 --> 17:23.450
Yeesh, what the hell
happened to you?

17:23.475 --> 17:24.543
I don't even know.

17:24.568 --> 17:25.635
There's a chance

17:25.660 --> 17:28.330
I was just
outsmarted by Hank.

17:28.573 --> 17:30.441
Can I get a hemlock!?

17:30.441 --> 17:32.310
At least you're not
a couple of outliers

17:32.310 --> 17:34.979
in a town full of liars!

17:34.979 --> 17:36.848
Davis, Karen,

17:36.848 --> 17:38.182
I have been lying

17:38.182 --> 17:39.813
and hiding
something from you.

17:39.838 --> 17:41.048
Get in line.

17:41.073 --> 17:44.010
No. I want
to confess to you now.

17:44.322 --> 17:45.656
Maybe you shouldn't.

17:45.656 --> 17:47.258
I'm not sure I want to know.

17:47.258 --> 17:48.059
Well, I do!

17:48.059 --> 17:49.660
So clam up
so she can tell us--

17:49.660 --> 17:50.728
Uh, you.

17:50.728 --> 17:52.108
Go ahead, Lacey.

17:52.133 --> 17:53.200
A while back,

17:53.225 --> 17:56.162
I was walking home
from the Foo Mart when...

17:57.134 --> 17:58.736
[humming nonchalantly]

17:58.736 --> 18:01.672
[yelps] Ouch! Hey!

18:01.672 --> 18:03.274
Ha! Catch much?

18:03.274 --> 18:04.876
Now throw it back.

18:06.800 --> 18:08.135
[window smashes]

18:08.346 --> 18:09.680
What the hell?

18:09.680 --> 18:12.350
The cops just told me
not to throw that around here.

18:12.350 --> 18:13.682
It was my final warning.

18:13.707 --> 18:15.843
[panicked sob]

18:15.868 --> 18:18.804
Ah, the old
panic and scram.

18:19.023 --> 18:20.091
Classic.

18:20.091 --> 18:22.226
That's the secret
that was eating you up?

18:22.226 --> 18:24.629
I took care of that
right after it happened.

18:25.470 --> 18:27.319
[panicked sob]

18:29.842 --> 18:31.711
Davis, Karen,
I broke your window.

18:31.736 --> 18:32.801
I'm really sorry.

18:32.904 --> 18:34.238
I'll pay for it.

18:34.238 --> 18:35.840
That was
back in the day

18:35.840 --> 18:37.708
when people
were honest.

18:37.708 --> 18:38.509
Except Lacey.

18:38.509 --> 18:42.246
Ah, so that's why
I couldn't crack Hank.

18:42.246 --> 18:44.115
There was no nut
to crack.

18:44.115 --> 18:45.449
Hank's nut-less!

18:45.449 --> 18:46.517
Thanks, Phil.

18:46.517 --> 18:47.894
Is this
a fresh keg?

18:47.919 --> 18:50.029
Oh, man,
is it ever.

18:50.054 --> 18:51.122
Overcompensating!

18:51.147 --> 18:52.207
He's lying!

18:52.232 --> 18:52.765
Yes!

18:53.019 --> 18:55.568
My lie detecting
is still on point.

18:55.593 --> 18:57.644
Why are you two
still moping?

18:57.669 --> 18:59.004
I told you the truth.

18:59.330 --> 19:01.198
Yeah, but
the rest of the town

19:01.198 --> 19:02.800
are still
big fat liars.

19:02.800 --> 19:04.402
Ah, get over
yourselves.

19:04.402 --> 19:06.003
Everyone lies
to everyone.

19:06.003 --> 19:07.605
Look at Helen
over there.

19:07.605 --> 19:09.473
She's lying so hard to Mavis

19:09.473 --> 19:11.342
about how cute
her ugly grandkid is,

19:11.342 --> 19:12.410
her hands are shaking,

19:12.410 --> 19:14.545
and Lanny's lying so hard
about the fish he caught,

19:14.545 --> 19:16.147
he's gonna throw his back out.

19:16.147 --> 19:18.549
People aren't excluding
you with their lies.

19:18.549 --> 19:20.418
If anything,
you're being included.

19:20.418 --> 19:21.485
So we're a part

19:21.485 --> 19:23.354
of everyone's
web of deceit?

19:23.354 --> 19:24.693
We're in-liars!

19:24.718 --> 19:26.052
Exactly.

19:26.156 --> 19:28.025
Hey, Zeke,
nice shirt.

19:28.095 --> 19:28.841
Thanks.

19:28.866 --> 19:29.934
I lied.

19:29.959 --> 19:30.760
You look stupid.

19:31.095 --> 19:32.430
Why would you--

19:32.430 --> 19:33.230
To liars

19:33.230 --> 19:35.033
and the lies
they lie!

19:35.058 --> 19:37.727
[cheering and laughing]

19:37.751 --> 19:38.812
[♪♪♪]

19:38.836 --> 19:43.174
There's your trust fund,
ya greedy little snot.

19:43.199 --> 19:44.534
120 bucks?

19:44.882 --> 19:46.216
I thought you said 250.

19:46.310 --> 19:47.820
Where's the rest?

19:47.845 --> 19:48.912
Well, I had
to buy a shovel,

19:49.246 --> 19:50.848
and a box of cigars

19:50.848 --> 19:52.984
so I could have something
to bury the money in.

19:52.984 --> 19:55.386
Plus I owed 40 bucks
at the hardware store,

19:55.386 --> 19:56.454
so I had to pay that

19:56.454 --> 19:58.322
before they'd sell me
the shovel.

19:58.322 --> 19:59.924
Oh, and I had lunch.

20:01.525 --> 20:03.394
Look at the up side.

20:03.394 --> 20:06.597
Not only did you
get 120 bucks,

20:06.597 --> 20:08.466
you got to pay off
some debt.

20:08.466 --> 20:11.135
It wasn't your debt,
but still...

20:11.135 --> 20:12.470
and you get
this shovel.

20:13.113 --> 20:15.249
I guess it's better
than nothing.

20:15.406 --> 20:18.075
I mean, it's close, but...

20:21.493 --> 20:23.602
You want this money
to re-sod the lawn,

20:23.627 --> 20:24.116
don't you?

20:24.141 --> 20:26.543
Kinda, yeah.

20:26.568 --> 20:27.618
You can have
the clue.

20:27.643 --> 20:28.852
I don't need a clue.

20:29.286 --> 20:31.155
It was the victim's son,

20:31.155 --> 20:32.523
behind the house,

20:32.548 --> 20:33.882
with the shovel.

20:33.907 --> 20:35.062
Repeatedly.

20:35.086 --> 20:37.734
[♪♪♪]

20:38.428 --> 20:39.972
[♪♪♪]

20:39.997 --> 20:42.666
I can't believe you carried that
burden of a non-secret

20:42.666 --> 20:43.442
for so long.

20:43.467 --> 20:46.137
I still carry the shame
of running away.

20:46.137 --> 20:47.204
Well, if it helps,

20:47.204 --> 20:48.806
you could pay me half
of what I paid

20:48.806 --> 20:49.567
for the window.

20:49.592 --> 20:50.659
Wait a minute.

20:50.784 --> 20:52.386
Insurance paid for that window.

20:52.543 --> 20:53.344
I approved it.

20:53.344 --> 20:56.902
Then what happened
to the money I paid?

20:56.927 --> 20:58.795
We, um...

20:58.949 --> 21:00.284
[chuckling awkwardly]

21:00.284 --> 21:01.886
The thing is, um...

21:01.886 --> 21:02.953
Liars!

21:02.953 --> 21:07.180
[♪♪♪]

21:07.224 --> 21:08.570
♪ I don't know

21:08.595 --> 21:10.998
♪ The same things
You don't know ♪

21:14.698 --> 21:16.489
♪ I don't know

21:16.514 --> 21:18.916
♪ I just... don't know

21:21.938 --> 21:24.073
♪ Ooh...

21:24.098 --> 21:25.433
♪ It's a great big place

21:25.458 --> 21:27.593
♪ Ooh...

21:27.618 --> 21:29.754
♪ Full of nothin' but space

21:29.779 --> 21:31.648
♪ Ooh...

21:31.673 --> 21:33.275
♪ And it's my happy place

21:33.300 --> 21:35.750
♪ I don't know ♪
